# ClassName Collision Management

## üö® CRITICAL: Global CSS Requires Unique ClassNames

**Since you're using GLOBAL CSS, className collisions will silently break components.** You MUST check for collisions and unused CSS EVERY time.

A duplicate className will override styles from other components - this is UNFORGIVABLE.

## Before Creating ANY New ClassName

### STEP 1: Search for collisions

```bash
# In your IDE, use Cmd+F (global search) for EACH new className
# Example: Before adding "task-card-header"
Search: "task-card-header"
# If ANY results appear (in CSS or TSX), choose a DIFFERENT name
```

**You MUST do this for EVERY className before using it.**

### STEP 2: Make it unique

```tsx
// ‚ùå COLLISION - Already exists elsewhere
<div className="card-header">

// ‚úÖ UNIQUE - Component-specific prefix
<div className="task-card-header">

// ‚úÖ UNIQUE - Creative but descriptive (if namespace crowded)
<div className="task-card-summit">  // "summit" = top of card
```

### STEP 3: Document the check (optional but recommended)

```tsx
// Checked: 'task-card-*' namespace clear as of 2025-10-08
export default function TaskCard() {
  /* ... */
}
```

## Choosing Unique ClassNames

### ‚ùå BAD - Too generic, likely to collide

```tsx
<div className="container">
<div className="header">
<button className="button">
<div className="wrapper">
<div className="box">
```

### ‚úÖ GOOD - Specific to component, unlikely to collide

```tsx
