## Automated Checks

### Check for duplicate classNames across codebase

```bash
# Find all className declarations
grep -r 'className=' --include="*.tsx" | cut -d'"' -f2 | sort | uniq -d
# Any output = COLLISION ‚Üí Fix immediately
```

### Check for unused CSS in a stylesheet

```bash
# For a specific stylesheet (example: workshop.css)
# 1. Extract CSS classNames
grep -o '\.[a-z-]*' styles/workshop.css | sort -u > css-classes.txt

# 2. Check each against all TSX files
while read class; do
  grep -q "$class" components/**/*.tsx || echo "UNUSED: $class"
done < css-classes.txt
```

## Creative Naming When Namespace Gets Crowded

If you have many similar components (e.g., multiple card types), use creative but clear names:

```tsx
// ‚ùå COLLISION RISK - Too generic
<div className="card-header">
<div className="card-body">

// ‚úÖ UNIQUE - Descriptive prefix
<div className="profile-card-header">
<div className="settings-card-header">
<div className="dashboard-card-header">

// ‚úÖ UNIQUE - Creative synonyms (when namespace is very crowded)
<div className="profile-card-summit">      // summit = top
<div className="profile-card-foundation">  // foundation = bottom
<div className="profile-card-spine">       // spine = main content
<div className="profile-card-wings">       // wings = side panels

// The creativity helps avoid collisions while staying memorable
```

## Collision Prevention Strategies

### 1. Component prefix

Start every className with component name:

```css
.user-profile-header {}
.user-profile-body {}
.user-profile-footer {}
```

### 2. Feature prefix

For shared UI, use feature name:

```css
.auth-form-field {}
.auth-form-button {}
.auth-form-error {}
```

### 3. Hybrid approach

Component + feature + element:

```css
.sidebar-nav-list {}
.sidebar-nav-item {}
.sidebar-nav-link {}
```

### 4. Creative descriptors

When namespace is crowded, use synonyms:

```css
/* All mean "background overlay" */
.modal-backdrop {}
.modal-scrim {}
.modal-veil {}

/* All mean "top section" */
.card-header {}
.card-summit {}
.card-crown {}
```

## ClassNames Enable Cmd+F Workflow

Every className must be easily findable via search. Use descriptive names that appear NOWHERE else.

**The workflow should be:**
1. Inspect element in browser
2. See className
3. Cmd+F in editor
4. Find code instantly

**If this fails, your naming failed.**

## REMEMBER

**Uniqueness > Brevity.** A longer, unique className is infinitely better than a short, colliding one.

**ALWAYS:**
- Search (Cmd+F) before creating a new className
- Make classNames component-specific
- Remove unused CSS classes
- Check for collisions regularly

**NEVER:**
- Reuse generic classNames (`container`, `wrapper`, `button`, `header`)
- Skip the collision check (it takes 2 seconds, saves hours of debugging)
- Leave unused CSS in stylesheets
- Create global utility classes (only humans create those)
